deck_excerpt: Traptrix meta deck with synchro package.
deck_description:
Here's in my opinion, the best Traptrix build with the synchro pacakge (Banshee, Agnimal and a synchro monster).

 

___Main Deck Explanation___

-Core of the deck : 3xTraptrix Pudica , 3xTraptrix Myrmeleo and 3xTraptrix Mantis are mandatory, (they're your starters, you have full combo with Traptrix Pudica and Traptrix Myrmeleo for example). 2xTraptrix Dionaea (1 to special from deck and set a trap, the second for mid game extender), 1xTraptrix Arachnocampa and 1xTraptrix Vesiculo (one of each as extenders for different situations). 1xTraptrip Garden (no need for more because of the 3 Traptrix Pudica), 3xTraptrix Holeutea mandatory, and 4 trap hole (2xGravedigger's Trap Hole  in case you draw one and still need protection against Nibiru, the Primal Being (or any other hand trap) with Traptrix Rafflesia; 1 Traptrix Trap Hole Nightmare, the best one; and 1 Bottomless Trap Hole to counter Fallen of Albaz, Snake-Eyes Flamberge Dragon, and many others (this one can be changed for any other trap hole or even totally removed)).

-Hand traps: 3xDimension Shifter is your best card, shutting down every meta deck (except Branded and Floowandereeze, that's where Bottomless Trap Hole helps :)), playing Dimension Shifter implies playing hand traps that *discards* themselves and not *send to the graveyard*, that's why we play 3xAsh Blossom & Joyous Spring, 2xGhost Mourner & Moonlit Chill and 2xGhost Belle & Haunted Mansion. Of course we have 3xInfinite Impermanence.

-Other : 2xTriple Tactics Talent for draw power instead of Pot of Prosperity because you need your extra deck. 1xAgnimal Candle for synchro summoning, 3xEvenly Matched in case you go second first game, and because you can discard it doesn't brick you.

___Extra Deck Explanation___

-Traptrix : One of each Xyz, 1xTraptrix Atypus to push for game, 3xTraptrix Sera best card overall.

-Other : 1xInfernal Flame Banshee (to search and summon Agnimal Candle), 1x a synchro monster (It should've been Baronne de Fleur but it got banned LOL, so for the list's sake I choose another Lvl 10 synchro boss monster), 1xTime Thief Redoer (to make with Traptrix Holeutea for full effect), 1xNumber 41: Bagooska the Terribly Tired Tapir for the grind game, and 1xDivine Arsenal AA-ZEUS - Sky Thunder. I choose to play Number F0: Utopic Future and Number F0: Utopic Draco Future (took the idea from Duel Evolution in their video https://www.youtube.com/@DuelEvolution ),

making them in the combo using the two leftover monsters. But for a budget friendly combo, thesee can be replaced with I:P Masquerena and Knightmare Unicorn. Finally 1xKnightmare Phoenix for more backrow removal (and to draw one when co-linked with Traptrix Sera).

-Alternative synchro monsters : Instead of Swordsoul Supreme Sovereign - Chengying, you can play Virtual World Kyubi - Shenshen, Draco Berserker of the Tenyi, or if you only want to synchro turn one, you can consider playing F.A. Dawn Dragster. I prefer playing a level ten in case I have to normal summon Dimension Shifter and synchro right away (thus making him relevant again in mid game).

___Side Deck Explanation___

Going First : 3xParallel eXceed, same as Nibiru, the Primal Being I don't like to draw it when I go second, so I side him in when going first. 1xCalled by the Grave if needed. 1xAnti-Spell Fragrance is just too powerful. Thankfully it got limited, but it is still very revelant in this spell-free deck (and look we're maining shifter so we don't need to pretend that this isn't toxic already...) 3xDimensional Barrier to defend against Voiceless Voice, Branded, or even the new Tenpai archetype.

Going Second : 2x Nibiru, the Primal Being, with shifter and evenly I don't think 3 is necessary, but you can still play 3 if you prefer (especially after this banlist making it stronger than before), and I don't like drawing it middle game, so I play it when I'm going second.  3xDroll & Lock Bird, not in main deck because not compatible with Dimension Shifter, but you can change them when siding. 2xLightning Storm for backrow removal (with a spell instead of monsters).

___Deck Combo___

Here's the best video to learn to play this deck (from Duel Evolution) : https://youtu.be/u8uiYzc4Meg?si=uTyC9_VxZWjI-WZp

It was way before the banlist but the idea is still the same (but this time without Baronne de Fleur).

 

I hope that helped ;) Enjoy !

deck_excerpt: "Nadie podrá evitar que nos apoderemos de Kaiba Corp."
deck_description: Siendo su carta insignia: el Dragon de 5 Cabezas un monstruo de fusion y no un monstruo ritual como nos mostraron en el anime, decidi adaptarles 2 cartas en particular para que pudiera invocarlo facilmente; ademas de añadir algunas cartas para que pudiera invocar factiblemente a su boss monster final: El Dragon Berserker

A fun, hopefully cheap, hard going second deck based around stealing the opponent's monsters and using them to get your batteries out on the field for their board removal combos. Made for Master Duel / Legacy of the Duelist (replace TTT with something like Upstart Goblin for LoTD).

The ultimate combo I have made with this is getting Mithra out on the field -> tributing her for Batteryman Charger -> special summoning 9-Volt -> adding Fuel Cell to hand which can then be special summoned -> tributing the Mithra token on the opponent's field for either Jizukiru or the Thunder King kaijus -> tributing Charger for Zaborg, and then destroying Jizukiru/Thunder King to send 9/10 cards from you opponent's ED to the GY. 9-Volt can then be tributed by Fuel Cell if need be to send one of your opponent's spells/traps to the GY.

We don't care about our own extra deck. All of the thunder monsters that Zaborg sends to our own GY gives Batteryman Industrial Strength more monsters to banish. There's probably some chaos monsters that would like banishing all of the light monsters in the GY, but I'm not smart enough to find synergy with that.

Batteryman synergizes well with monarchs and kaijus -- you can tribute 9-Volt after it helps get Fuel Cell on the field to return a kaiju on your opponent's field to your hand, for example, and the destruction from zaborg and kaiju slumber also help turbo out Industrial Strength. We don't need Batteryman Solar for this, in fact he slows things down.

deck_name: WIP Hero list post April 2024 list
deck_excerpt: Vision Hero Destiny Hero Xtra Hero Elemental Hero Masked Hero
deck_description:
Mali going to 3 adds multiple lines to the list, that I think justifies some of the more unusual cuts and sides here that detract from convential hero deck theory.

Vyon + discard = Wonder Driver + DPE(normal Vyon send Mist add Mali banish mist add Poly poly make Dangerous discard card send Denier banish Mali special Mali make Wonder Driver banish Mali special 3rd Mali trigger Wonder set Poly special Denier poly make DPE, extend further deepending on hand)

AHL + discard accomplishes the same thing(special Stratos add Vyon normal Vyon send Mist etc etc) 

Faris pitch name is still the ideal line but having a low ceiling low investment line in a 1.5 card combo to set up half of your board is why Fusion Destiny is in the side now, you can board it in by going -1 Vyon -1 Mask Change -1 Angel in matchups where plopping down a DPE asap or Dystopia burn is relavent(it would be the best card in the deck if it didn't lock to dark hero imo)

Cutting Liquid and Abzero is another possibly contrivertial pick which I made because in games I found both cards rarely came up and I'd always rather see a vyon/stratos/faris in my hand, + miracle fusion is better used to make Wake Up or Neos Wingman to close games out going blind second or into grind game, which is more relavent and came up in testing games way more often. Trimming down to 40 cards is a plus.

You might consider running Masked HERO Divine Wind when Tenpei comes around, although I'm not running it yet because making Blast in the first place rarely comes up if at all, let alone Divine Wind.

deck_name: Blind Second Sky Striker (Post April 2024 Banlist)
deck_excerpt: UNLIMITED ENGAGE... UNLIMITED POWEEEERRRRR!!! FOUR MORE YEARS OF SKYSTRIKER!
deck_description:
The April 2024 banlist was definitely an emotional roller coaster for me, especially when I saw that Raye's ace card - Engage - is now UNLIMITED!!! Engage back to three means that Sky Striker is definitely at FULL POWER and MORE, since more support has come out since then! Now you can blow through your opponent's board with even more ease with 25+ boardbreaker cards and enough advantage + consistency to finish off your opponent! Engage, engage and engage your way to victory with Blind Second Sky Striker!

FOUR MORE YEARS OF SKYSTRIKER! RAYE IS BAE! RAYE IS ETERNAL! TOSS FORMAT FOREVER! LETS GOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOO

Raye can now reliably fight toe-to-toe with the top meta contenders in the TCG, especially when backed with an incredible arsenal of blind-second field wipes such as Evenly Matched, Triple Tactics Talent and Change of Heart! Nuke the board, surgically eliminate your opponent's card and outgrind them in a game of resources with TRIPLE ENGAGE!

The philosophy with Blind Second Sky Strikers is to wipe out most if not all of your opponent's resources that they slap down on the board going first, and then close out the match with Sky Striker's unparalleled grind game.

This deck has cards specifically picked out for the April 2024 meta, like Triple Tactics Talents/Thrust (super good since duelists often monster effects during your turn or handtraps you) and 7 monster stealing cards (particularly good at cracking Snake-Eye boards).

The current meta allows for Evenly Matched and Raigeki to obliterate most duelist's boards this format since they spend all their resources building their "unbreakable" board only to fall to 1-2 cards - allowing your Sky Striker gameplan to go off unhindered and out-resource your opponent.

If your weakened opponent hasn't surrendered yet due to the sheer resource advantage and offensive pressure this deck generates, you can clear the board with a plethora of cards including Linkage, allowing Raye to OTK all by herself!

If you have any questions about this deck, feel free to ask me in the comments below!

GLHF Duelists!

Want to see the deck in action? Scroll to the very bottom for the Youtube video!

deck_excerpt: colossus, spright, spright blue, competitive, locals, thunder dragon, thunder, gigantic, level 2, deep sea diva, little knight, iblee
deck_description: Competive and fun spright deck for locals. Play it as you would normal spright and colossus is just a bonus!

60-card version. You can test in several ways by placing the 2x "Pressured Planet Wraitsoth" Field in place of the Enemy Controller in the main deck.

 

The idea of Kashtira is the same as the pure Snake Eye deck, which is that they are bodies on the field for you to continue plays if you are interrupted by the opponent's hand traps and interactions. You can access Reprodocus to make a Dinosaur Token on the opponent's field with Lost World and with another extender make Donner, Dagger Fur Hire to destroy it and with the protection of the field continue your plays.

 

Otherwise the deck continues to focus on doing what Dinosaur does best: Dolkka + Tyranno + Omega + Lost World protecting the target field from monsters because I always use this play to avoid Evenly Matched or Lightning Storm etc and the main thing is that is having Miscellaneousaurus from Follow Up in GY.

My idea is not to do like most people who use Dinosaur with a bunch of bricks like Normal Monsters to make a move that loses to all the opponent's hand traps, including Nibiru, and even if the move stops Dinosaur does not separate the interactions, so a Dark Ruler No More and your field is completely off, I think about turn 3 too.

The deck now no longer has Linkuriboh and Baronne de Fleur so turn 1 the use of the Ground Xeno engine is weaker and also access to Double Evolution Pill because without Linkuriboh there is no longer Secure Gardna. That's why going according to these card combinations that I've included will give you better results.

 

This is a version to go second and below I will leave the main combo of the deck going first:

 

https://www.duelingbook.com/replay?id=813757-59506491

Combo: Archosaur + Petiteranodon

End Board: Tyranno + Dolkka + Omega + Horned Saurus + Lost World /in Hand: Polymerization

  (token on the opponent's field to protect from target cards and blind second cards and I forgot to add Polymerization to the hand but do it)

 

The only detail I would like to leave is that despite Linkuriboh being a big loss, it is also something beneficial for the end board because with Kaitoptera cards we now always have access to Lost World and without Linkuriboh this means that target protection and against cards blind second such as Evenly Matched and Lightning Storm is very efficient and the chance of stopping the opponent is much greater.

Things to note because of different format limitations:

Pot of Prosperity - Should be at 3 in the Main Deck, just remove the one Change of Heart, you can run this deck at 42 cards no problem

Raigeki - At 3, you can main this and remove either Chalice or Cosmic depending on match up

Hey! Just decided to post a very F2p Dmaid list for either beating some Solo duels or learning the basics of Dragonmaid of course if you have access to higher rarities then just go to a branded deck profile. A general end board would just be Spheres + Tidying pass with maybe an Earlie or Sheou (Rarely), You have the ability to also mess around and maybe make synchro plays using one of your many Revival spells & Shrine. I've heard some hype about a Bystial engine but in a normal / "Pure" Dmaid deck Chamber is your only target for a banish.

Decided to share the new format brew: Runick Spright with Melffy engine.
The deck is heavy on board breakers since in the runick deck your flex slots need to be high powered, but also versatile.
Only cards I considered cutting after matches were Onibimaru(Potentially for 3rd Hugin) and Nibiru (For either droll or Lava Golem)

By now the deck was tested in a high powered local against:
Fire-King Snake-Eyes (9 wins out of 11 matches)
Labrynth (4 wins out of 4 matches)
Voicless voice (3 wins out of 4 matches)
Thunder-Dragon Bystials (1 win out of 3 matches) (Your spright spells plus them which feels horrible)
Pure spright (2 wins out of 2 matches)
Thus the winrate is almost 80% (19/24)

Good luck duelists!

This deck is based on pulls through Ancient sanctuary. 

Going into Invasion of Chaos, we decided to switch it up, and legacy ban the Chaos monsters. Wanted to experience old Yugioh without the inheritance of Chaos influence. 

We will unban the Chaos monsters come, 5D's era.
Current list

This deck is based on pulls through Rise of Destiney. 

We are including side sets, and have a special "extra pack" option at the end of each match. This feature lets us add X amount of packs from a set that we've already opened. Gives the players more chances to pull needed cards. Once you pull from the set, you can't pull again from it.

This deck is based on pulls through Lost Millenium. 

We made it to GX era! The plan is to slow down the packs and take it one at a time going forward.
